sentences: John O'Driscoll Preston (1950–2017) was a British music industry executive.
He was educated at Shrewsbury School followed by Trinity College, Oxford, where he studied history, and University of Liverpool, where he earned a degree in Latin American history in 1972.
Preston started his career with Bruce's Record Shops in Scotland, then joined EMI in 1977.
In 1984, he was managing director of Polydor Records UK.
Preston was the managing director of RCA Records UK from 1985 to 1989, and chairman of BMG from 1989 to 1998.
